## Validity vs Relay: Side-by-Side

| Check | Result | Enforced By |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `VerifyScript()` | TRUE | All full nodes (consensus) |
| `IsStandardTx()` | FALSE | Default-policy relay nodes |
| `AreInputsStandard()` | FALSE | Default-policy relay nodes |
| Includable in a block | YES | Miners may include |
| Will propagate via P2P | NO | Default policy drops it |
| Network reach | None | Never reaches miners through gossip |

## Rejection Code Path (Bitcoin Core)

```
// policy/policy.cpp — AreInputsStandard
for (unsigned int i = 0; i < tx.vin.size(); i++) {
    const CTxOut& prev = mapInputs.AccessCoin(tx.vin[i].prevout).out;
    std::vector<std::vector<unsigned char>> vSolutions;
    TxoutType whichType = Solver(prev.scriptPubKey, vSolutions);
    if (whichType == TxoutType::SCRIPTHASH) {
        // Extract the redeemScript (last push of the scriptSig)
        CScript subscript(vSolutions[0].begin(), vSolutions[0].end());
        TxoutType whichType2 = Solver(subscript, ...);
        if (whichType2 == TxoutType::NONSTANDARD)
            return false;        // failure point for this transaction
    }
}
```

`Solver(52935587)` returns `TxoutType::NONSTANDARD` because the bytes match no entry in `solver.cpp`.

RPC error returned by `sendrawtransaction` / `testmempoolaccept`:

```
error code:    -26
error message: bad-txns-nonstandard-inputs
```

## Paths to Broadcasting Non-Standard Scripts

- **Testnet3** — default `-acceptnonstandardtxs=1` accepts it at relay.
- **Mainnet (default policy)** — submit out-of-band to a mining-pool API.
- **Standard alternatives** — Taproot script-path spends are standard regardless of inner-script content.
- **Protocol path** — propose a BIP that adds the desired template to `Solver()`.
